<subSubSection pageId="153" pageNumber="551" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="153.[1389,2599,301,728]" pageId="153" pageNumber="551">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1392,1751,458,487]" pageId="153" pageNumber="551">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Vulnerable on The IUCN Red List. The Oku Mouse Shrew is known from very few specimens across a very small and severely fragmented distribution; its extent of occurrence is estimated to be ¢.9300 km®. It may be threatened by habitat destruction through logging operations and the conversion of land to agricultural use.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
